<DocLayout title="Ricuci — VP3" lang="en">
  <h1>VP3 — PFAFF / Husqvarna Viking</h1>
  <p class="docs-lede">
    VP3 is the "new" PFAFF/Husqvarna format. It supports structured
    multi-color designs, thread metadata (chart, description, catalog), and
    multiple hoops. It is an HUS body compressed with EmbCompress, wrapped
    in a tree of format sections.
  </p>

  <h2>What it supports</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Trims</strong>: supported.</li>
    <li><strong>Colors</strong>: thread objects with extended (manufacturer-style) metadata.</li>
    <li><strong>Hoop</strong>: stored in the format.</li>
    <li><strong>Compression</strong>: EmbCompress (<a href={withBase('en/docs/embcompress')}>see</a>).</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Reference tooling</h2>
  <p>
    Cross-verified against the pyembroidery reader (MIT). The writer is
    <strong>software-verified</strong>; acceptance on a real machine is
    still pending, as for HUS / VIP.
  </p>

  <p class="docs-prevnext">
    <a href={withBase('en/docs/formats/jef')}>← JEF</a>
    <a href={withBase('en/docs/formats/exp')}>EXP →</a>
  </p>
</DocLayout>